1
00:00:05,862 --> 00:00:10,091
Open your borders!

2
00:00:10,445 --> 00:00:11,500
Done.

3
00:00:12,736 --> 00:00:14,998
Really?

4
00:00:18,651 --> 00:00:20,331
Amazing!

5
00:00:20,590 --> 00:00:23,668
You actually made this website?

6
00:00:23,668 --> 00:00:23,670
You actually made this website?
Can everyone see this now?

7
00:00:23,670 --> 00:00:25,725
Can everyone see this now?

8
00:00:25,730 --> 00:00:27,885
Not public yet.

9
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:31,325
Make it public.
You put in all this work.

10
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:36,784
King and the others probably
don't get how awesome this is.

11
00:00:38,182 --> 00:00:40,342
Maybe you can become friends with him.

12
00:00:47,531 --> 00:00:49,032
Ready?

13
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,800
Yeah.

14
00:01:21,570 --> 00:01:23,824
What is this?

15
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:28,365
"Let's ignore DOnoko."

16
00:01:31,310 --> 00:01:32,710
It's not my fault...

17
00:01:32,710 --> 00:01:35,078
"Yes! Let's ignore her."

18
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:38,217
I have to delete it.

19
00:01:53,096 --> 00:01:59,500
THE RIGHT TO JUDGE

20
00:03:00,163 --> 00:03:03,166
No balls in the hallway!

21
00:03:03,776 --> 00:03:06,688
Kenta, isn't it game time soon?

22
00:03:06,690 --> 00:03:09,632
You don't want to hurt yourself.
Go play in the gym.

23
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,808
All right.

24
00:03:18,354 --> 00:03:23,851
You really didn't see the
last person who was with Mr. Haryu?

25
00:03:24,982 --> 00:03:26,582
Yeah...

26
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:34,440
We heard Haryu arguing with someone...

27
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:41,611
But by the time we got there,
the culprit was already gone.

28
00:03:42,754 --> 00:03:49,100
Feeling responsible,
Haryu went after them alone...

29
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:56,600
That's the last I saw him.

30
00:04:11,005 --> 00:04:13,236
It's my fault...

31
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:17,100
I should have protected him!

32
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,857
Please calm down.

33
00:04:18,857 --> 00:04:18,860
Please calm down.
It's not your fault.

34
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:21,600
It's not your fault.

35
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:25,600
He promised he'd be right back!

36
00:04:25,805 --> 00:04:28,600
Is there anything else you remember?

37
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:31,600
No, I've told you everything.

38
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:35,600
Anything that could lead
us to the culprit. Anything?

39
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:43,600
The DVD...

40
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:47,680
The footage that was supposed
to be in the time capsule was missing.

41
00:04:48,271 --> 00:04:52,100
I'm sure the culprit took it out.

42
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:03,100
Maybe they were
worried they'd be exposed.

43
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:06,600
Where’s that DVD now?

44
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:12,980
At first, I thought Ms. Ohtani had it...

45
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:15,600
but he doesn’t either.

46
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,100
Understood.

47
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,940
Thank you for your cooperation.

48
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:26,900
Please catch him quickly.

49
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,600
Otherwise...

50
00:05:32,315 --> 00:05:34,600
I might take care of him myself...

51
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:43,600
Is there anything we can do?

52
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:54,600
I don’t want to just
wait around to be killed.

53
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:05,348
Alright, I’m off.

54
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:14,600
Me too.

55
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:38,600
Dad! Why are you here?

56
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:42,100
I was nearby, so I decided to pick you up.

57
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,600
Awesome.

58
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:51,040
- Goodbye, Mr. Mori.
- Goodbye.

59
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,880
Mori?

60
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:10,600
Dad?

61
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,920
Stop... Stop!

62
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,429
You finally noticed.

63
00:07:27,430 --> 00:07:30,600
What did you do to Chonmage!

64
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,100
Dad!

65
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:46,100
Kanon, that...

66
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:48,600
Sorry, Kanon, but that...

67
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:52,600
- A ball flew this way!
- Everyone get inside.

68
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:55,600
Is anyone hurt?

69
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:05,100
- Dad, are you okay?
- Yeah.

70
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:08,600
I have some things to do,
so you head on home.

71
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:12,600
No way, this feels scary...

72
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:28,740
Mori is a teacher at Takasato Elementary?

73
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:33,100
Yeah, he also had the DVD.

74
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:36,100
So that means Mori was, after all...

75
00:08:36,115 --> 00:08:41,800
If he’s a teacher,
he might've dug up the capsule

76
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:45,140
and reburied it with the album.

77
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:50,600
Mori knew you were Kanon's dad, right?

78
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:54,600
So why has he been
pretending not to know until now?

79
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:59,100
You finally noticed.

80
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:03,340
- Let's take this to the police.
- We can't.

81
00:09:03,526 --> 00:09:05,100
Why not?

82
00:09:05,528 --> 00:09:07,600
Because if he...

83
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:15,600
If he killed Chonmage and
the others, I won't forgive him.

84
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,165
Won't forgive? What will you do?

85
00:09:18,165 --> 00:09:18,170
Won't forgive? What will you do?
I don’t know!

86
00:09:18,170 --> 00:09:21,100
I don’t know!

87
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:26,600
But if he gets caught,
we still won’t know anything!

88
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:30,600
Anything! The reason behind the killings.

89
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:36,600
Still, if we don’t catch him,
you and King aren't safe.

90
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:40,976
- We have to go to the police!
- I said we can’t.

91
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:44,900
Are you being serious?

92
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:47,100
This isn’t the time to be saying that!

93
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,571
You might get killed!

94
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,600
I’m not going to die!

95
00:09:52,850 --> 00:09:58,600
It's not like they catch
the culprit and that’s it.

96
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:16,100
You delinquent employee!

97
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:18,100
Shino...

98
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,100
Hmm.

99
00:10:20,603 --> 00:10:22,100
What's this?

100
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:25,100
I emailed you the interview audio too.

101
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:28,100
You got this scoop,
so you should write it.

102
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:30,400
You write it.

103
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:34,600
I don't know what you're
up to, but we miss you.

104
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,600
- See you!
- Bye.

105
00:10:56,375 --> 00:10:58,600
What’s wrong?

106
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,100
I should be the one asking.

107
00:11:01,375 --> 00:11:03,600
Did something happen at school?

108
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:07,100
I know.

109
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:10,600
Ever since the reunion, things have been off.

110
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:16,600
Well, it’s not just me.
Kanon’s senses it too.

111
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,100
She’s scared.

112
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,100
So please.

113
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:28,100
Stay by Kanon’s side.

114
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,600
Just a little more...

115
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,600
Of what?

116
00:11:39,450 --> 00:11:44,100
Just a little more time
and it should be over.

117
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:53,100
I’m talking about being her father.

118
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:58,150
As her dad, just be there for her.

119
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:03,600
But it has to be me.

120
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:11,600
Right now you have to be Kanon’s dad.

121
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,600
No one can take your place.

122
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,600
No?

123
00:12:56,384 --> 00:13:00,016
"Mori"

124
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:06,600
No luck, huh...

125
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,976
We can't just give up.

126
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,600
Hello.

127
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:50,100
Teacher, look.

128
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,600
Welcome home.

129
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,100
Kanon’s homeroom teacher, Mr. Mori.

130
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:57,100
This was super tough to make.

131
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:59,100
- Can I try one?
- Yeah.

132
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:01,600
These are awesome!

133
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:11,450
Kanon is really a great kid.

134
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:13,950
Cheerful and kind.

135
00:14:16,450 --> 00:14:20,450
Unlike you, she values her friends.

136
00:14:20,450 --> 00:14:25,450
Of course, she doesn’t bully anyone either.

137
00:14:28,968 --> 00:14:35,250
Also, it seems you didn't remember me.

138
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:43,450
Even though we’ve met
so many times. You’re awful.

139
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:50,450
I've been watching closely and I knew.

140
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:58,225
Really... you’re the worst.

141
00:14:59,882 --> 00:15:04,450
I became a teacher to make sure
scum like you don’t get born.

142
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:09,950
People who bully others
end up being scum even as adults.

143
00:15:14,225 --> 00:15:18,200
I’m actually known to be
quite a good teacher!

144
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,450
Haven’t you heard from Kanon?

145
00:15:22,950 --> 00:15:26,450
So please, don’t get in the way.

146
00:15:29,450 --> 00:15:31,450
Don’t mess with me.

147
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:41,450
We’re not trying to just pretend
nothing happened, either.

148
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:45,450
We’re trying to face things
properly and live on.

149
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:47,950
What right do you have to stop us?

150
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:53,300
It was you guys that killed her.

151
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:56,950
You’re the ones that started all this.

152
00:15:56,950 --> 00:16:00,400
What do you mean you're "facing things properly."

153
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:05,950
You only remember the convenient
parts. What part of that is facing it?

154
00:16:05,950 --> 00:16:09,450
You probably don’t even
remember bullying DOnoko.

155
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:12,950
A- bout that...
- Stop, stop! Stop.

156
00:16:14,450 --> 00:16:19,950
As a teacher, I have the responsibility to
guide my students in the right direction.

157
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:23,450
I’m different from you guys.

158
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:28,500
So either don’t get in the way,

159
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:31,500
or just get killed already.

160
00:16:36,950 --> 00:16:39,450
You...

161
00:16:39,450 --> 00:16:41,950
- Teacher—
- Kanon!

162
00:16:41,950 --> 00:16:44,950
Well then, see you at school.

163
00:16:44,950 --> 00:16:48,450
Sorry for interrupting your work.

164
00:16:58,950 --> 00:17:01,450
Why didn’t you catch him?

165
00:17:01,450 --> 00:17:03,950
I couldn’t in front of my daughter.

166
00:17:06,450 --> 00:17:10,450
I mean, is he really the culprit?

167
00:17:10,450 --> 00:17:12,950
Huh? Of course he is.

168
00:17:12,950 --> 00:17:15,776
Tabo, calm down.

169
00:17:16,450 --> 00:17:20,450
I don’t think it’s him.

170
00:17:20,450 --> 00:17:22,250
Yukki and I investigated.

171
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:25,450
He wasn't home, so we asked
around the neighborhood.

172
00:17:25,450 --> 00:17:29,950
I didn’t expect him to be at your house though.

173
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:32,450
But thanks to that,
we got to hear a lot of things.

174
00:17:32,775 --> 00:17:37,450
Mori is said to be polite and a nice person.

175
00:17:39,950 --> 00:17:43,950
It’s surprising they talked to us
considering the times right now.

176
00:17:45,950 --> 00:17:48,450
I apologize!

177
00:17:48,450 --> 00:17:52,450
I mentioned the Shukan Apollo.

178
00:17:55,057 --> 00:17:56,950
You can't do that.

179
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:59,950
Yeah, sorry.

180
00:17:59,950 --> 00:18:01,950
Sorry.

181
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:05,450
This is kinda nice.

182
00:18:05,825 --> 00:18:10,450
A friend's in trouble, so you
gather and fight together!

183
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:14,450
It’s like The Doraemons!

184
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:23,950
Since we’re all here anyway,
don’t fight and help each other out.

185
00:18:23,950 --> 00:18:26,450
Um...

186
00:18:26,450 --> 00:18:28,450
What’s The Doraemons?

187
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:31,950
What! You don’t know The Doraemons?

188
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:35,650
They had this phone card gadget and—

189
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:36,525
A phone card?

190
00:18:36,530 --> 00:18:39,950
Oh you really have no clue!

191
00:18:39,950 --> 00:18:41,950
You know, I'm glad.

192
00:18:41,950 --> 00:18:48,500
I thought an adults apologizing
to an adult would be this harsh thing.

193
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:50,950
But it was kind of cute.

194
00:18:50,950 --> 00:18:53,450
- That was a deep!
- Was it!

195
00:18:53,450 --> 00:18:55,450
Where did you learn that?

196
00:18:55,450 --> 00:18:57,450
Did I...

197
00:18:59,950 --> 00:19:02,450
Manage to apologize properly?

198
00:19:04,950 --> 00:19:07,450
Why all of a sudden.

199
00:19:09,350 --> 00:19:11,450
Mori said to me:

200
00:19:12,134 --> 00:19:17,950
"You only remember what suits you."

201
00:19:19,525 --> 00:19:24,950
He said that I probably don’t even
remember the things I did to you.

202
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:30,450
It’s frustrating, but I think he was right.

203
00:19:34,973 --> 00:19:38,950
Samurai have chonmage topknots.

204
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:41,450
Chonmage...

205
00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:43,450
Hey, teacher's coming!

206
00:19:43,450 --> 00:19:45,450
Let's go!

207
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:49,950
- Forgot my shoes!
- What are you doing?

208
00:19:49,950 --> 00:19:51,625
Let’s go, let’s go.

209
00:19:51,630 --> 00:19:53,950
Chonmage!

210
00:19:53,950 --> 00:19:56,450
Let’s play cops and robbers.

211
00:20:01,725 --> 00:20:09,950
But, even if he forgot,
Mori was in the group, right?

212
00:20:09,950 --> 00:20:18,450
If that’s the case, it means
he was also bullying Saruhashi, right?

213
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:23,870
I'm not pointing fingers or anything but,

214
00:20:23,872 --> 00:20:29,450
it's odd that Mori would hold a grudge like this.

215
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:32,450
Ah, there he is!

216
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:34,450
King...

217
00:20:36,218 --> 00:20:38,750
I heard you made this website.

218
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:40,950
Chonmage told me.

219
00:20:40,950 --> 00:20:43,950
It’s nothing special...

220
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:48,950
By the way, we’re about to
play dodgeball. Wanna join?

221
00:20:49,575 --> 00:20:50,950
Really?

222
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,950
Of course! Let's be friends.

223
00:20:54,450 --> 00:20:56,575
- Nice, it’s settled!
- Let’s go!

224
00:20:57,530 --> 00:20:59,241
Let's decide teams.

225
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:03,950
- Rock, paper...!
- Wait, wait...!

226
00:21:05,464 --> 00:21:08,450
Mori! Mori!

227
00:21:20,575 --> 00:21:27,450
Even if Mori is the culprit, what's the motive?

228
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:36,950
I don’t know. It's just...

229
00:21:39,450 --> 00:21:40,950
What is it?

230
00:21:42,450 --> 00:21:44,950
No... I’m sorry.

231
00:21:46,950 --> 00:21:52,450
We hurt someone without even realizing it.

232
00:21:54,450 --> 00:21:57,299
Running away from the inconvenient past.

233
00:21:58,980 --> 00:22:01,050
But that doesn't mean...

234
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:04,650
We can’t do anything about it.

235
00:22:06,950 --> 00:22:10,950
Or else it doesn't sit well with me.

236
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:41,800
I’m sorry!

237
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:05,367
Did you make up with Mr. Mori?

238
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:11,800
You make up after a fight.
That's what you said.

239
00:23:17,379 --> 00:23:19,025
Kanon.

240
00:23:23,675 --> 00:23:25,300
You know...

241
00:23:27,025 --> 00:23:29,391
I was a bad kid.

242
00:23:36,815 --> 00:23:39,300
You look like you're doing alright.

243
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:45,300
I guess people are more
forgiving when you're pretty.

244
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:55,300
I can't write the article anymore.

245
00:23:57,775 --> 00:24:00,300
Oh, really...

246
00:24:03,425 --> 00:24:06,150
Are you quitting?

247
00:24:07,225 --> 00:24:12,430
I used to think it was fun.

248
00:24:12,430 --> 00:24:12,434
I used to think it was fun.
Or that it was funny.
I assumed they didn't care.

249
00:24:12,434 --> 00:24:17,439
Or that it was funny.
I assumed they didn't care.

250
00:24:19,650 --> 00:24:26,448
I would hurt others with
that kind of selfish attitude.

251
00:24:28,875 --> 00:24:30,975
You did?

252
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,800
I was...

253
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:44,800
A bully.

254
00:24:53,825 --> 00:24:57,800
No way! You wouldn’t be mean.

255
00:24:58,125 --> 00:25:00,300
Because you're always kind to me...

256
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:07,125
Of course, now I don’t want to be mean.

257
00:25:07,775 --> 00:25:10,130
And I'm careful not to be.

258
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:15,300
But I used to be different.

259
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:21,800
What? Are you blaming me?

260
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:32,300
I knew that my articles could
greatly change someone’s life...

261
00:25:34,230 --> 00:25:40,025
That I could end up being the perpetrator to someone,

262
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:45,527
and I thought I was writing with that in mind.

263
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:54,800
But it was nowhere near enough.

264
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:00,300
Nor was my resolve...

265
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:04,300
I was naive.

266
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:10,200
I’m not quitting being a reporter.

267
00:26:12,554 --> 00:26:21,825
From now on, I’ll write as if I were the perpetrator.

268
00:26:23,775 --> 00:26:26,125
I’ll write with stronger resolve.

269
00:26:28,820 --> 00:26:31,300
I’ll face it thoroughly.

270
00:26:34,075 --> 00:26:36,800
You're a good guy.

271
00:26:37,375 --> 00:26:41,580
You taught me to ride a bicycle,

272
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:41,583
You taught me to ride a bicycle,
cheered on my gymnastics,
and you work hard.

273
00:26:41,583 --> 00:26:47,589
cheered on my gymnastics,
and you work hard.

274
00:26:49,225 --> 00:26:51,800
So it’s okay.

275
00:26:52,150 --> 00:26:56,075
If you apologize properly,
Mr. Mori will forgive you.

276
00:26:57,300 --> 00:27:02,300
Mr. Mori is kind, so I'm sure
you guys can make up.

277
00:27:02,604 --> 00:27:04,606
I will help too.

278
00:27:29,300 --> 00:27:33,800
I will keep facing it, no matter what.

279
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:44,300
Suffer properly as the perpetrator.

280
00:27:47,649 --> 00:27:54,656
I’ll keep reading your articles too.

281
00:27:55,657 --> 00:28:00,800
So... Please don’t quit being a reporter.

282
00:28:07,300 --> 00:28:10,900
My goal is...

283
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:17,679
to live strongly so this never happens again.

284
00:28:23,685 --> 00:28:25,800
Thank you.

285
00:28:26,125 --> 00:28:30,325
I’m Tomoya Mori.

286
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:32,800
Yes.

287
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:36,300
Ah, okay, got it.

288
00:28:36,698 --> 00:28:40,300
I'll go to the staff room and check.

289
00:28:40,300 --> 00:28:41,800
Yes.

290
00:28:48,175 --> 00:28:50,710
Mori is really there, right?

291
00:28:50,710 --> 00:28:50,712
Mori is really there, right?
Don’t worry, the school confirmed it.

292
00:28:50,712 --> 00:28:53,715
Don’t worry, the school confirmed it.

293
00:28:54,800 --> 00:28:58,300
Wait a minute, how did you get that info?

294
00:29:00,075 --> 00:29:01,723
I know, I know!

295
00:29:01,723 --> 00:29:05,425
I’ll make sure to apologize to Saruhashi later.

296
00:29:07,300 --> 00:29:08,800
Hmm?

297
00:29:09,375 --> 00:29:11,733
Was that...

298
00:29:14,990 --> 00:29:18,590
These parents are unbelie—

299
00:29:18,590 --> 00:29:20,590
Miss Takaki?

300
00:29:25,475 --> 00:29:29,590
No... that...

301
00:29:30,325 --> 00:29:32,754
Because of this, you’re fighting with Dad, right?

302
00:29:33,755 --> 00:29:34,590
That’s not—

303
00:29:34,756 --> 00:29:37,090
Teacher, I’m sorry!

304
00:29:38,025 --> 00:29:40,425
Wait, stop... stop!

305
00:29:46,175 --> 00:29:48,590
Why did you have to say something like that?

306
00:30:01,175 --> 00:30:09,375
I wasn’t a good kid at all, and
I’m not even a respectable adult.

307
00:30:11,793 --> 00:30:20,802
Yet I act like I'm perfect,
telling Kanon this and that.

308
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:25,075
I’m tired of that now.

309
00:30:27,809 --> 00:30:35,590
I didn’t marry you because you
were a good kid or a great person.

310
00:30:35,590 --> 00:30:41,090
I married you because
I thought we could be good parents.

311
00:30:42,125 --> 00:30:46,828
It’s looks like it's gonna take
more time than I thought.

312
00:30:48,590 --> 00:30:50,590
Sorry.

313
00:30:52,090 --> 00:30:55,090
Oh, I think it’s done.

314
00:30:55,525 --> 00:30:57,090
Move, move.

315
00:31:04,590 --> 00:31:06,590
Alright?

316
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:11,090
Hang in there.

317
00:31:11,650 --> 00:31:15,275
I will make delicious sweet red beans.

318
00:31:18,350 --> 00:31:19,590
Thank you.

319
00:31:20,175 --> 00:31:21,590
Hmm! This is...

320
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:29,150
Hello?

321
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:45,590
That mustn’t be seen by anyone.

322
00:31:48,100 --> 00:31:50,590
I’m a respectable teacher.

323
00:31:53,130 --> 00:31:58,090
I'm not bullying anyone,
and I never have.

324
00:31:58,090 --> 00:32:01,590
Who’s inside there?

325
00:32:03,590 --> 00:32:09,590
They’re the ones who bullied her.
But I didn’t bully anyone.

326
00:32:13,915 --> 00:32:18,090
If they think I'm their friend,
I’ll be killed too.

327
00:32:18,090 --> 00:32:20,090
No, no, no!

328
00:32:24,926 --> 00:32:26,928
"What you say might be hurtful."

329
00:32:26,928 --> 00:32:29,090
It’s your fault...

330
00:32:31,590 --> 00:32:34,590
Everything. Everything...!

331
00:32:34,590 --> 00:32:37,090
Everything, everything!

332
00:32:45,947 --> 00:32:49,090
I'm definitely not at fault.

333
00:32:53,275 --> 00:32:54,590
Hey, King!

334
00:33:00,175 --> 00:33:04,090
Please give that back.

335
00:33:11,325 --> 00:33:12,700
No.

336
00:33:16,625 --> 00:33:19,590
Do you want to be a bad kid too?

337
00:33:20,475 --> 00:33:23,450
You need to make up with Dad.

338
00:33:23,450 --> 00:33:27,090
I won’t make up with your dad.

339
00:33:28,775 --> 00:33:30,992
We weren't close in the first place.

340
00:33:31,090 --> 00:33:35,090
That’s a lie. Dad wanted to make up.

341
00:33:43,004 --> 00:33:45,090
Just give it back!

342
00:33:52,090 --> 00:33:54,590
Damn it...

343
00:33:58,090 --> 00:33:59,590
Thanks.

344
00:34:09,450 --> 00:34:11,590
Mori.

345
00:34:12,325 --> 00:34:13,590
Kanon...

346
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:19,590
This is not what it looks like.

347
00:34:20,675 --> 00:34:23,590
I just wanted the DVD.

348
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:27,090
So, this is...

349
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:34,450
Are you okay?

350
00:34:34,450 --> 00:34:35,590
Yeah...

351
00:34:39,300 --> 00:34:41,590
Kanon.

352
00:34:41,590 --> 00:34:46,590
Let’s return that DVD to your teacher.

353
00:34:50,071 --> 00:34:52,590
But...

354
00:34:53,074 --> 00:34:57,590
I heard it’s really important to him.

355
00:35:02,083 --> 00:35:03,590
Right?

356
00:35:19,090 --> 00:35:21,090
I’m sorry.

357
00:35:34,115 --> 00:35:36,117
Ah, King!

358
00:35:39,120 --> 00:35:43,124
Um, well, this is...

359
00:35:44,125 --> 00:35:45,875
Sorry for the trouble.

360
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:48,090
It seems my daughter forgot something.

361
00:35:49,130 --> 00:35:55,136
I need to talk with Mr. Mori for a bit.
Can you go home with Dad’s friends?

362
00:35:57,090 --> 00:35:58,590
Let’s go.

363
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:12,100
Yukki!

364
00:36:12,100 --> 00:36:14,900
Oh, Kanon.

365
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:16,600
Where’s King?

366
00:36:18,100 --> 00:36:19,600
He’s with Mori.

367
00:36:19,600 --> 00:36:21,550
Huh? Then I’ll go too.

368
00:36:21,550 --> 00:36:23,600
No!

369
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:26,600
Dad and Mr. Mori are making up.

370
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:29,100
That’s not what I meant.

371
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:33,100
Koyama, let’s wait for now.

372
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:39,180
I’m not at fault!

373
00:36:39,825 --> 00:36:42,100
Because of you guys.

374
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:45,186
I'm a good teacher too.

375
00:36:46,500 --> 00:36:50,100
- You guys are the ones at fault.
- I know that!

376
00:36:56,100 --> 00:37:01,600
Hin, Kantaro, Niko...

377
00:37:03,470 --> 00:37:05,600
And Chonmage too!

378
00:37:08,100 --> 00:37:10,100
They died.

379
00:37:10,100 --> 00:37:12,100
Because of me.

380
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:19,810
Tabo's being targeted, Sonoko's suffering.
Toyo and Yukki are getting caught up in it!

381
00:37:20,910 --> 00:37:24,610
If I were better, none of this
would be happening.

382
00:37:26,227 --> 00:37:27,980
I know that.

383
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:31,560
Then take responsibility
and just die already.

384
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:34,100
Yeah but...

385
00:37:37,450 --> 00:37:40,100
I can’t just die.

386
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:49,590
I have a family and friends too.

387
00:37:50,810 --> 00:37:55,540
Even though it’s my fault,
they said told me to not give up.

388
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:01,600
Even Chonmage...

389
00:38:02,830 --> 00:38:05,400
Nust have been really scared...

390
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:10,470
He stayed alone so he
wouldn’t bother anyone...

391
00:38:18,279 --> 00:38:22,283
He didn’t run away like you did.

392
00:38:23,810 --> 00:38:25,530
I didn’t run away.

393
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:27,640
I’m doing my best—

394
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,600
It’s okay!

395
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:33,294
No matter what you think, I’ll accept it.

396
00:38:35,296 --> 00:38:40,301
I won’t run away either.

397
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:50,311
What’s done can’t be undone, but...

398
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,600
Even so...

399
00:39:00,100 --> 00:39:05,600
A bad kid can to try to become a good kid, right?

400
00:39:17,100 --> 00:39:19,100
The truth is...

401
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:22,600
I wanted to help.

402
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:31,600
I was happy.

403
00:39:31,600 --> 00:39:38,100
That Chonmage remembered me.

404
00:39:41,612 --> 00:39:43,600
Because I was happy...

405
00:39:45,940 --> 00:39:48,100
Mori!

406
00:39:48,100 --> 00:39:50,600
But still...

407
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:53,600
Why did you kill them?

408
00:39:55,100 --> 00:39:57,100
Why did you kill them!

409
00:39:57,100 --> 00:39:58,600
Chonmage!

410
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:00,600
No... I...!

411
00:40:02,383 --> 00:40:05,600
I was the one who let you join our group.

412
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,600
That’s not it!

413
00:40:12,100 --> 00:40:14,016
I will...

414
00:40:15,396 --> 00:40:17,600
I will put an end to this!

415
00:40:18,399 --> 00:40:23,100
I couldn’t do anything.

416
00:40:24,600 --> 00:40:27,100
I did nothing.

417
00:40:31,412 --> 00:40:34,600
I couldn’t even delete the site.

418
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:44,100
I couldn’t do it.

419
00:40:45,900 --> 00:40:48,760
Even though I knew they were
writing bad things about DOnoko...

420
00:40:52,980 --> 00:40:57,100
Because that was...

421
00:40:57,121 --> 00:41:00,600
One day Hin...

422
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:02,600
In the forest Kantaro...

423
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:06,260
Hey, let's just call Mori by his name.

424
00:41:06,260 --> 00:41:08,280
Huh?

425
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:12,600
A forest path with Mori and Chonmage…

426
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:14,100
You're a pair.

427
00:41:14,100 --> 00:41:16,100
- I like that.
- Is that okay?

428
00:41:16,100 --> 00:41:19,600
- I like it.
- Okay! Let’s go.

429
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:21,100
Yeah.

430
00:41:27,100 --> 00:41:31,100
I really wanted to help.

431
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:50,100
You...

432
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:58,100
After all, I’m a good teacher.

433
00:42:08,510 --> 00:42:09,980
My name is Misa Adachi.

434
00:42:09,980 --> 00:42:12,600
What’s your dream for the future?

435
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:15,600
My dream is to be a zoo director.

436
00:42:15,600 --> 00:42:17,600
My name is Toshiki Takeda.

437
00:42:17,600 --> 00:42:20,600
What’s your dream for the future?

438
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:24,600
My dream is to fly in the sky.

439
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:27,300
Why do you want to fly in the sky?

440
00:42:28,100 --> 00:42:31,100
I want to be a firefighter in the future.

441
00:42:31,100 --> 00:42:32,533
I’m Emi Nakajima.

442
00:42:32,533 --> 00:42:35,100
What’s your dream for the future?

443
00:42:35,100 --> 00:42:39,160
I want to become an idol who can sing and dance.

444
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:42,100
I want to be a samurai!

445
00:42:42,100 --> 00:42:43,840
A samurai?

446
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:45,260
Is that no good?

447
00:42:45,260 --> 00:42:47,130
No, it’s totally fine.

448
00:42:47,131 --> 00:42:48,600
That’s cool.

449
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,600
I’m Yuki Hanawa.

450
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:52,600
What’s your dream for the future?

451
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:56,557
Mine is to become a bride!

452
00:42:56,600 --> 00:42:58,600
I’m Kengo Toyokawa.

453
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:00,340
What’s your dream for the future?

454
00:43:00,340 --> 00:43:03,100
My dream is to be a charismatic hairstylist.

455
00:43:03,100 --> 00:43:04,920
Charismatic?

456
00:43:04,920 --> 00:43:06,900
I’m Takahiro Koyama.

457
00:43:06,900 --> 00:43:09,570
What’s your dream for the future?

458
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:12,600
My dream is to be an astronaut.

459
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:16,600
Go to America, join NASA, and train...

460
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:20,600
My dream is to become a
hero and defeat the bad guys.

461
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:23,100
- A hero?
- Yeah.

462
00:43:23,100 --> 00:43:25,600
You might actually become one.

463
00:43:25,600 --> 00:43:28,600
Teacher, don’t get so serious.

464
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:39,060
My goal is to live strongly so
this will never happen again.

465
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:41,602
Well then, please go ahead.

466
00:43:41,860 --> 00:43:43,600
I’m Tomoya Mori.

467
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:53,600
My dream is to always be friends with
Hin, Kantaro, Niko, Tabo, Chonmage, and King.

468
00:43:58,100 --> 00:44:01,600
Huh? There’s more...

469
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:09,800
Now, please tell us your name
and your dream for the future.

470
00:44:10,600 --> 00:44:12,820
I’m Shion Seto.

471
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:21,600
Do you remember now?

472
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:23,600
Who is that?

473
00:44:28,100 --> 00:44:30,100
DOnoko.

474
00:44:35,360 --> 00:44:37,658
The other...

475
00:44:38,896 --> 00:44:41,660
Donoko.

476
00:44:43,100 --> 00:44:47,500
My dream is
to become a pianist.
